UMAR MUHAMMED, A 30-year-old man, James Samuel, has reportedly  hanged himself  in a classroom at the Government Secondary School  in Gurku, Karu Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. Sunday PUNCH learnt  that the Tiv man   from  Benue State killed himself  on Friday night. A  police officer  serving in Abuja  resident in the area was said to have  found the man dangling from the ceiling of the classroom. He was said to have reported  the matter to the Gurku Police Outpost. Our correspondent learnt that the police found two childhood pictures of the  man  and that of his mother at the scene, but no suicide note. The body was brought down in  the presence of the police and taken to a health facility by family members. A Tiv community leader in Gurku who is also the   deceased’s father identified only as Chief Samuel,   said, “He was popular among his peers. He is Tiv but understood Gbagyi, Jaba, Hausa and Gwandara  languages. “I learnt that this is the first suicide in the history of Gurku and that it is taboo. “My late son attended Government Secondary School Gurku. He was a farmer, welder and a traditional drummer.” Confirming the incident to our correspondent, the paramount ruler of Gurku, Alhaji Jibrin Waziri,  who spoke through an aide, Zubairu Adamu, said he  had visited the scene of the incident. Copyright PUNCH.
